10/06/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A co-operation agreement was signed on Thursday (9 June) in Belgrade by the heads of the national labour bureaus of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia and Slovenia. 
During the conference, participants pledged to exchange information and experiences regarding employment and to focus co-operation on the creation of a borderless labour market in the region. 
A central topic was the challenge of youth employment, considered one of the most pressing problems.
In other news, economy ministers from the region are in Sofia on Friday, attending a conference on investments and trade in Southeast Europe. 
This is the fourth such meeting of its kind. 
(Danas, Mediapool, news.bg - 10/06/05; Tanjug, Beta - 09/06/05)
